    {
      "beat_id": "B08",
      "act": "THE EXPONENTIAL",
      "estimated_duration_s": 12,
      "narration_text": "A constant instantaneous loss rate becomes exponential survival only after a Markov-style step: the reservoir has short memory and the same fractional amount is lost per unit time. Then survival is e to the minus Gamma t.",
