      "act": "ENVIRONMENT ENGINEERING",
      "estimated_duration_s": 12,
      "narration_text": "The density of photon modes can change radiative decay. A resonant cavity may enhance emission; a photonic band gap may suppress it. But matrix elements, polarization, geometry, and spectral matching matter too.",
